Sam’s Kitchen was one of the eateries we chose to visit while in Hawaii. The atmosphere was one of a “hole in the wall spot.” The menu had a variety of items that could please almost everyone in your party.  From the person who likes to try it to the individual that dares to eat everything. The taste took a little getting use but overall I think the food was good. And customer service was great; we were greeted before we even entered and while we waited in line the manager continued to check on us. We had a little wait before we ordered but it wasn’t so long to deter us. One thing I definitely want to mention is seating. There aren’t a lot of tables there so seating goes fast. We arrived in the evening/night (maybe around 6pm-8pm) and we waited for a table to clear to have a “sit and eat” experience. Overall this location is a go-to spot in Honolulu for anyone visiting Hawaii. Definitely try something at Sam’s Kitchen.
